{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"aac96940-5f1e-4aea-ad9f-ce4565df4f1d","content":"On macOS, if your NativeAOT app crashes and `createdump` isn't available, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Enable macOS core dumps:**\n   ```bash\n   ulimit -c unlimited\n   ```\n\n2. **Find the crash report:** macOS automatically writes crash reports to:\n   ```\n   ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   ```\n   Look for a `.ips` or `.crash` file matching your process name.\n\n3. **Get a core dump via `lldb`:** If you need a full core dump rather than just the crash report, reproduce the crash under `lldb`:\n   ```bash\n   lldb ./your-app\n   (lldb) run\n   # after crash:\n   (lldb) process save-core /tmp/core.dump\n   ```\n\n4. **Analyze with `lldb`:** Open the core dump:\n   ```bash\n   lldb ./your-app -c /tmp/core.dump\n   (lldb) bt          # backtrace\n   (lldb) thread list\n   (lldb) register read\n   ```\n\n5. **Check `/cores/`:** macOS may also write cores to `/cores/core.<pid>` if the system is configured to do so (check with `sysctl kern.corefile`).\n\n**Key note:** NativeAOT binaries include native debug symbols (if built with debug info), so `lldb` can resolve frames directly — no DAC or SOS needed, unlike CoreCLR dumps.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bb6f43a2-5576-4611-81bc-2d2578b107bf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about recovering crash dumps on macOS for NativeAOT apps when `createdump` is not available. This seems like a general knowledge question about .NET NativeAOT debugging on macOS. Let me check if there's any relevant documentation in the repository first.","outputTokens":431,"requestId":"6013:15FDF:DEC4BA:1024E76:69EACB2D"},"id":"3eabc89b-233f-4942-b087-839b75d6373f","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:45:28.574Z","parentId":"2a045f1d-7f12-4680-93bd-adc69f58c390"}
